quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  30,51,"And if We send a wind which turns their crops yellow, behold they will become even more firm in their disbelief"
  30,52,"O Prophet, you cannot make the dead hear you, nor can you make the deaf hear your call especially when they have turned their backs and are running away"
  30,53,nor can you guide the blind out of their error. None will hear you save those who believe in Our revelations and submit themselves as Muslims
  30,54,"It is Allah Who has created you in a state of helplessness as a baby, then gave you strength to come out of helplessness in youth, then after strength again helplessness and grey hair in old age. He creates whatever He wills and it is He Who is the All- knowing, the Almighty"
  30,55,"On the Day when the Hour of Judgement will be established, the criminals will swear that they did not stay in this world more than an hour; thus are they ever deluded"
  30,56,"But those who are given knowledge and faith will say: \"In fact you have stayed, according to the Book of Allah, till the Day of Resurrection and this is the Day of Resurrection: but you were not aware"
  30,57,"On that Day, no excuse of theirs will avail the wrongdoers, nor will they be allowed to seek forgiveness"
  30,58,"The fact is that We have set forth every kind of example for men in this Qurâ€™an, but whatever sign you may bring, the unbelievers are sure to say: \"You are preaching falsehood"
  30,59,Thus Allah has set a seal on the hearts of those who do not use their common sense
  30,60,"So O Prophet, have patience: surely the promise of Allah is true; and do not let those, who themselves have no certainty of faith, shake your firmness"